<br>
Part I:<br>
<br>
After deliberating and planning for weeks, Clan McCulloch marches onto the tundra to meet the forces of the Wrath Orcs, under the leadership of their Cheiftain Redwind. The Northmen had sent emmissaries to Kaladim, in an effort to gain Dwarven favor, but the reception from the Underfoot was less than warm. In the end, Clan McCulloch was to stand alone against the hordes of Orcs spilling onto the tundra of Everfrost, or so they thought...<br>
<br>
Unlike their Dwarven cousins, the Gnomes of the Underfoot were curious about this young barbarian clan, and sent two representatives to Everfrost to aid Hrothdan and his forces. Another Gnome would join his bretheren later in the battle. <br>
<br>
The air was still, strangely still for autumn, yet in the distance, war clouds gathered thick as night. Redwind ordered his forces from their holes in the ground just as Clan McCulloch and the Gnomes of the Blackmaul Crusaders reached the battle site, a small plain containing some ruined structures including an ancient tower... <br>
<br>
Squeaker studies the lay of the land.<br>
Hrothdan prepares a speech.<br>
Hrothdan looks to his gathered friends.<br>
You tell your raid, 'Sons an' daughters o' Halas tonight we fight fer teh safety o our homes'<br>
Glug, glug, glug... Andora takes a swig of Bottle of Kalish.<br>
You tell your raid, 'Teh Orcs have threatened our people fer centuries. We'll endure their aggression nae longer!<br>
You tell your raid, 'Me father, an' me father's father spilled their blood fer teh safety o Halas'<br>
You tell your raid, Tonight we follow our ancestors an' take up teh sword against our enemies!'<br>
Cidwm cheers.<br>
Agaar growls.<br>
Horen emits a low rumble and then roars like a lion!<br>
You tell your raid, 'For when teh night is through, teh tundra will be painted with Orc Blood!'<br>
Cidwm howls.<br>
Erulaga nods and prepares.<br>
Agaar growls, &quot;My blade craves flesh!!&quot;<br>
Hrothdan raises his axe defiantly.<br>
You tell your raid, 'Tonight teh Wrath Orcs will come tae fear the names....'<br>
You tell your raid, 'McCulloch and Blackmaul!'<br>
You emit a low rumble and then roar like a lion!<br>
You tell your raid, 'Fer Halas!<br>
Horen cheers.<br>
You tell your raid, 'Fer Halas!'<br>
Cidwm raises his stick and howls.<br>
You tell your raid, 'Fer Halas!'<br>
Agaar says, 'For Halas!!'<br>
Hrothdan tries to control his horse amid the wild cheers of his war host.<br>
Cidwm says, 'Fer Justice an Home!'<br>
Cidwm growls.<br>
Cidwm tells the raid, 'They be out there, let's be ta it!'<br>
Agaar holds his mount also, spooked by the bloodlust!<br>
<br>
<br>
McCulloch's scouts had been away for hours without any word. The allies stood with nerves on edge, waiting for any sign of their hated foe. By mid afternoon the silence on the tundra would be replaced by the clang of steel on steel, and the cries of the dying... <br>
<br>
Cidwm says, 'Things be clear, but still be ready ta bash. A good feelin.'<br>
Erulaga nods.<br>
Erulaga says, in Barbarian, 'aye'<br>
You tell your raid, 'I hear them comin' lads! Prepare yerselves!'<br>
You tell your raid, 'Tae battle lads! Fight!'<br>
Agaar growls, &quot;My blade craves flesh!!&quot;<br>
You say, 'Fer Halas and Clan McCulloch!'<br>
You emit a low rumble and then roar at a snow orc shaman.<br>
Cidwm says, 'Arroooo! Sink yer fangs inta a snow orc shaman.'<br>
Squeaker waves goodbye to a snow orc shaman.<br>
Squeaker emits a low rumble and then roars at a snow orc shaman.<br>
a snow orc shaman says 'Orc stomp, orc kill - orc weapons, your blood will spill.'<br>
You cheer.<br>
You say, 'Pray tae whatever gods motivate ye Orcs! Pray that they keep ye safe because only teh gods can keep me from rippin' ye apart!'<br>
Hrothdan bangs on his shield three times.<br>
You emit a low rumble and then roar like a lion!<br>
Hrothdan charges into battle like a crazed animal.<br>
Hrothdan howls.<br>
Cidwm growls.<br>
You say, 'Fer Halas and Clan McCulloch!'<br>
You emit a low rumble and then roar at a snow orc trooper.<br>
Hrothdan fights with abject fury.<br>
<br>
<br>
In the midst of battle, shrill cries could be heard on the wind. The Redwind had been preparing his forces for this day, for a very long time. The earth trembled as orcish archers charged into battle, shooting flame-tipped arrows from the safety of two-story towers set on top of fully armored mammoths, trampling all who were unlucky enough to be in their destructive path...<br>
<br>
Squeaker tells the raid, in Barbarian, 'Mammoth riders!'<br>
Cidwm says, 'Arroooo! Sink yer fangs inta an orcish mountaineer.'<br>
Squeaker tells the raid, in Barbarian, 'It be a slaughter!'<br>
a snow orc trooper says 'Orc stomp, orc kill - orc weapons, your blood will spill.'<br>
Hrothdan howls with rage'<br>
<br>
<br>
The battle raged for a few hours before the Clan McCulloch and allies stopped the first Orc advance. Although the fighting had calmed with the coming of night, Hrothdan knew the Orcs didn't fear the shadows. In fact, they embraced the darkness, and used it to their advantage in battle. There would only be time for a short rest...<br>
<br>
You tell your raid, 'Me friends.. we need tae rest a bit. Teh Orcs will come again with teh growin' shadows.'<br>
You tell your raid, 'Teh bloody Orcs are tamin' Mammoths'<br>
Squeaker tells the raid, in Barbarian, 'Aye that was some fierce fighting'<br>
Erulaga says, in Barbarian, 'Wow that was awesome'<br>
You tell your raid, 'Bloody bastards'<br>
Hrothdan shouts.<br>
You say, 'Is that all ye have Redwind?'<br>
Squeaker cheers at Agaar.<br>
Squeaker says, in Barbarian, 'I saw 2 orcs get away Hrothdan'<br>
You kneel down.<br>
Hrothdan pulls a knife from his pack, and with a swift cut, scalps the corpse of his enemy.<br>
You grin evilly.<br>
Squeaker says, in Barbarian, 'I would expect them to report this... '<br>
Hrothdan shakes his head.<br>
You say, 'They'll nae see tomorrow, little one. Me sister is trackin' 'em as we speak.'<br>
Andora tells the group, in Barbarian, 'Never fear! Andora's here! a snow orc trooper is no match for me!'<br>
<br>
<br>
The allies barely had time to bandage their wounds before the scouts reported another orcish advance moving rapidly under cover of darkness...<br>
<br>
Squeaker tells the raid, in Barbarian, 'Stand to! They are right behind me!'<br>
You emit a low rumble and then roar at a snow orc trooper.<br>
Hrothdan charges into battle like a crazed animal.<br>
Cidwm tells the raid, 'I'm chasing one o' teh filth!'<br>
You tell your raid, 'Tae battle brothers an' sisters! Dinnae give 'em any quarter!'<br>
Cidwm says, 'I'll be showing it a Northman's fury!'<br>
You tell your raid, 'They charge again! Stand To!'<br>
You tell your raid, 'I hear teh ground thunderin'! Ye gods what a battle!'<br>
You tell your raid, 'By teh Six Hammers! We be yer executioners, ye slimy, pig-snouted, waste o' flesh!'<br>
You tell your raid, 'Fight on me clan! Fight like yer very souls depended on it!'<br>
Cidwm nods.<br>
You tell your raid, 'Ye gods!'<br>
You tell your party, 'Stand to! a wooly mammoth wishes tae face us in battle! Prepare yerselves!'<br>
Agaar growls, &quot;My blade craves flesh!!&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
