<br>
You bow before Erulaga.<br>
Cidwm cheers.<br>
You beam a smile at Erulaga.<br>
You tell your raid, 'Brothers an' sisters our enemy flees like teh cowards they are. They'll be back though. Ye can be sure o' that.'<br>
Agaar nods at Hrothdan.<br>
You tell your raid, 'Me scouts tell me teh Orcs are ridin' on Spiders now.'<br>
You tell your raid, 'More abominations'<br>
Cidwm tells the raid, 'They be gettin some other kinda leadin. They nae be smart enough fer all these plans!'<br>
Ottoe giggles.<br>
You raise an eyebrow inquiringly.<br>
You peer around intently<br>
Erulaga points at ottoe come to where they can see ya.<br>
Agaar says, 'Ottoe?'<br>
Cidwm glares.<br>
You peer around intently.<br>
You say, 'Another squeaker?'<br>
Cidwm says, 'another finger wiggler?'<br>
Erulaga says, in Barbarian, 'aye the latter.'<br>
Ottoe smiles.<br>
Agaar is confused by these little folk.<br>
Cidwm nods at Ottoe.<br>
Agaar snaps to attention and salutes Ottoe crisply.<br>
Erulaga says, in Barbarian, 'Hallo ottoe and welcome.'<br>
You tell your raid, 'Tis good tae have ye little ones! Stand fast along side o' us!'<br>
<br>
<br>
Ottoe had come just in time, for out of the night shrill cries echoed through the surrounding hills. As the allies anxiously searched for the source of the cries, they were met by the stares of a thousand glowing red eyes. The eyes were arranged in neat vertical rows of eight, and steadily rushed towards the Northmen and their allies...<br>
<br>
Squeaker tells the raid, in Barbarian, 'Gah! They ambusehd me! Spider riders and Mammoth riders, along with their Orcish vanguard!'<br>
Squeaker tells the raid, in Barbarian, 'Look to the south, comrades!'<br>
Cidwm tells the raid, 'Ready fer a beatin, they are. Bring them ta me wee one!'<br>
You tell your raid, 'Bloody hell! Come tae mee ye abominations! I'll nae go down without sendin some o' ye tae teh underworld ahead o' me!'<br>
a snow orc trooper says 'Orc stomp, orc kill - orc weapons, your blood will spill.'<br>
a snow orc mountaineer says 'Orc stomp, orc kill - orc weapons, your blood will spill.'<br>
You tell your raid, 'Tae Agaar me friends! He's bein' mauled!'<br>
Squeaker says, in Barbarian, 'No Mercy!'<br>
Agaar tells the group, 'My health grows weak...'<br>
Agaar looks pale and tired.<br>
Agaar goes into a berserker frenzy!<br>
Agaar growls, &quot;My blade craves flesh!!&quot;<br>
Cidwm says, 'Arroooo! Sink yer fangs inta a gigantic wooly spider.'<br>
You tell your raid, 'Fight as if all teh demons o' Araluu were on yer heels lads!'<br>
Hrothdan goes into a berserker frenzy!<br>
<br>
<br>
Like the previous waves of Orcs, the allies turned this charge as well. The storm intensified, and conditions became so harsh, that fighting became impossible. The allies were weary at this point, and secretly praised their individual deities for the respite. Hrothdan in particular wondered if Xelita and Tahranu were correct is saying that Lord Karana's power extended to the tundra of Everfrost. Was it he that sent the storm? The chieftain had no time to ponder this. His remaining war host needed looking after... <br>
<br>
Hrothdan tends to Hrothdan's wounds by applying a foul smelling, sickly yellow colored salve.<br>
You begin to bandage yourself.<br>
Agaar tells the group, 'Maybe it would be wise for us all to rest while the storm rages.'<br>
Hrothdan nods<br>
You tell your raid, 'Bring teh wounded tae teh tower, an' post scouts along teh surroundin' hills. We rest in teh tower till teh storm lets up.'<br>
Cidwm tells the raid, 'Rest! We be Northmen in battle! Rest be fer storytellin after.'<br>
Horen tells the raid, in Barbarian, 'Aye!'<br>
Erulaga sits and holds his head.<br>
Squeaker tells the raid, in Barbarian, 'Did all survive the day?'<br>
Cidwm nods at Squeaker.<br>
Erulaga tells the raid, in Barbarian, 'Aye. We all did.'<br>
Hrothdan looks at the carnage through blood soaked eyes.<br>
You tell your raid, 'Teh first day is ended friends!'<br>
You tell your raid, 'Victory be ours!'<br>
Agaar looks exhausted.<br>
You tell your raid, 'Fer Halas an' Teh Underfoot!'<br>
Horen cheers.<br>
Cidwm tells the raid, 'The Tribunal ruled against the orcs.'<br>
Cidwm says to Agaar, 'Lad ye need be slayin yer foe, like a true man o the north.'<br>
Hrothdan tends to his friends, cheking their condition before resting himself.<br>
Cidwm tells the raid, 'I thank ye wee ones. Hoping I get ta meet some o yer mates. I hear they be dwarven. *grins*'<br>
You say, 'Ye've done well lads'<br>
You say, 'Teh Orcs will be back though. We cannae let our guard down yet. Have teh watch on teh hills signal if they attack again.'<br>
Squeaker tells the raid, in Barbarian, 'I don't think any escaped to warn Chief Redwind'<br>
You tell your raid, 'Nay. Our scouts killed their runners.'<br>
Agaar growls at the mention of Redwind!<br>
Squeaker says, in Barbarian, 'May I make a fire to cook with?'<br>
You say, 'Aye General. We need warmth as well as rest.'<br>
You say, 'Come tae teh fires lads. We all need tae keep warm.'<br>
Squeaker prepares her fire and begins her stew.<br>
Ottoe holds out his hands flaming, in front of Squeaker.<br>
Squeaker says, in Barbarian, 'Thanks dear'<br>
Squeaker feels good without the breeze.<br>
Ottoe says, in Barbarian, 'Its so cold here!'<br>
Squeaker says, in Barbarian, 'Darn tootin '<br>
Agaar says, 'Barbarian ale will warm you wee ones.'<br>
Erulaga nods in aggrement with Ottoe.<br>
Squeaker tells the raid, in Barbarian, 'Nothing like heated grease to warm the bones'<br>
Ottoe tells the raid, in Barbarian, 'I must know your feelings of Innoruuk, Hrothdan. It is my understanding that you worship Rallos Zek, ally to Innoruuk.'<br>
Squeaker tells the raid, in Barbarian, 'Aye alot of my clan frowns upon the god of war'<br>
You tell your raid, 'Nay Ottoe'<br>
You tell your raid, 'We worship a pantheon.'<br>
You tell your raid, 'All of us have patron deities, but we all recognize teh pantheon'<br>
Agaar says, 'I have no alliance to Innoruuk or Bertox friends, though Zek is my patron deity.'<br>
You tell your raid, 'Marr blesses us with valor from our birth, teh Tribunal guides our everyday lives, spurring us tae action when need be, and Zek gives us strength in battle. <br>
Ottoe tells the raid, in Barbarian, 'Would you protect someone that follows Innoruk, Bertox, or Cazic Thule?'<br>
Hrothdan grins then spits.<br>
You tell your raid, 'Never. Tae ye we seem barbaric, but we understand more'n ye realize, little one.'<br>
You grin evilly.<br>
Ottoe tells the raid, in Barbarian, 'Then I think we could drink together as friends'<br>
You tell your raid, 'That be welcome little one'<br>
You bow before Ottoe.<br>
Ottoe tells the raid, in Barbarian, 'I am a follower of the Nameless, myself.'<br>
Ottoe bows before Hrothdan.<br>
<br>
<br>
As the storm pelted the tower with snow and wind, a bond formed between the allies that, at first, seemed weak and fractured when the war began. As the Northmen and Gnomes rested their weary limbs, exchanging stories from their people's history, a most unlikely young barbarian traveller sought refuge from the storm...<br>
<br>
You say, 'Welcome lad. Ye may enter.'<br>
Tarbon says, 'Aye, thank ye, sir'<br>
Tarbon says, 'Was by luck that I happened to run by this place'<br>
You say, 'Have ye come tae pledge yer sword fer us or tae observe?'<br>
Agaar says, 'I am Agaar, Warrior of Clan McCulloch.'<br>
Tarbon bows.<br>
Cidwm says, 'Go play, me pup.'<br>
Cidwm`s warder says 'As you wish, oh great one.'<br>
Tarbon says, 'An honor, Agaar'<br>
Squeaker says, in Barbarian, 'I don't believe in luck during battles'<br>
Squeaker says, in Barbarian, 'I say we search him.'<br>
Tarbon says, 'And as fer yer question, sir, I have come to observe... I have little to offer '<br>
You say, 'Tarbon ye can watch over this tower, then. We use it fer a bandage station, an' yer help would be most welcome.'<br>
Squeaker says, in Barbarian, 'Can we trust him?'<br>
Squeaker says, in Barbarian, 'It be conveninet he shows up now'<br>
You say, 'I think we can'<br>
